WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:12.262 --> 00:00:15.640 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO] Hey bartender,
you're a detective, too?

00:00:15.724 --> 00:00:18.059 position:50% align:center
That works out perfectly.

00:00:18.143 --> 00:00:20.478 position:50% align:center
No bartender, just a dude.

00:00:20.562 --> 00:00:23.064 position:50% align:center
And that's my own stash,
so stop chuggin' it.

00:00:23.148 --> 00:00:25.859 position:50% align:center
Come to think of it, I don't
remember anyone mentioning

00:00:25.942 --> 00:00:28.486 position:50% align:center
why half of the office
is set up like a bar.

00:00:28.570 --> 00:00:30.613 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
It's a relic of the past.

00:00:30.697 --> 00:00:32.407 position:50% align:center
Before Inugami took us in,

00:00:32.490 --> 00:00:34.868 position:50% align:center
he apparently ran the
agency with a partner.

00:00:34.951 --> 00:00:37.454 position:50% align:center
He says the bar schtick
was their thing.

00:00:37.537 --> 00:00:39.289 position:50% align:center
He's not that interested
in running it,

00:00:39.372 --> 00:00:40.832 position:50% align:center
so he lets it be.

00:00:40.915 --> 00:00:42.250 position:50% align:center
A partner?

00:00:42.334 --> 00:00:43.710 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] We don't know
where they are now, 

00:00:43.793 --> 00:00:45.253 position:50% align:center
but keep it to yourself.

00:00:45.337 --> 00:00:46.838 position:50% align:center
It's a sensitive subject.

00:00:46.921 --> 00:00:48.548 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Mm. I understand.

00:00:48.631 --> 00:00:52.427 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO] Whatever! I just
need someone to listen!

00:00:52.510 --> 00:00:57.515 position:50% align:center
♪

00:02:23.101 --> 00:02:25.895 position:50% align:center
There's this wonderful
woman I really like.

00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:27.188 position:50% align:center
But the truth is,

00:02:27.272 --> 00:02:29.566 position:50% align:center
I don't actually know the
first thing about her.

00:02:29.649 --> 00:02:31.943 position:50% align:center
Not her real name,
or how to reach her.

00:02:32.027 --> 00:02:33.528 position:50% align:center
Maybe she's just not into you?

00:02:33.611 --> 00:02:37.407 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO] No, that's not true!
She's always so nice to me!

00:02:37.490 --> 00:02:40.368 position:50% align:center
But I need to know so
much more about her.

00:02:40.452 --> 00:02:43.246 position:50% align:center
If only I could tell her how
much my heart aches for her.

00:02:43.329 --> 00:02:45.248 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA] Sounds like you
love a coy woman!

00:02:45.331 --> 00:02:46.833 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's right, I love her!

00:02:46.916 --> 00:02:48.168 position:50% align:center
His love's coy?

00:02:48.251 --> 00:02:49.252 position:50% align:center
[KON]
Koi?

00:02:49.336 --> 00:02:50.962 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO]
I gotta go take a leak.

00:02:51.046 --> 00:02:52.797 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
S'back there.

00:02:52.881 --> 00:02:54.549 position:50% align:center
[KON]
I happen to love koi, too!

00:02:54.632 --> 00:02:57.635 position:50% align:center
The ones down at the park are
especially plump and tasty.

00:02:57.719 --> 00:02:59.763 position:50% align:center
She's not that kind of koi!

00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:03.350 position:50% align:center
It's sweet, huh?
We should give this guy a hand!

00:03:03.433 --> 00:03:05.852 position:50% align:center
There's nothing better
than a good love story!

00:03:05.935 --> 00:03:08.897 position:50% align:center
And besides, even you were
born out of the love between 

00:03:08.980 --> 00:03:11.274 position:50% align:center
your human father and
kemono mother, weren't you?

00:03:11.358 --> 00:03:14.152 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI grunts]
Gross! Don't talk about that!

00:03:14.235 --> 00:03:16.905 position:50% align:center
Shiki was born out of love?

00:03:16.988 --> 00:03:19.991 position:50% align:center
Hey. Is something wrong, Kabane?

00:03:20.075 --> 00:03:21.743 position:50% align:center
It's what Akira said.

00:03:21.826 --> 00:03:25.413 position:50% align:center
That hanyo are born out of love
between humans and kemono?

00:03:25.497 --> 00:03:26.706 position:50% align:center
That makes me think.

00:03:26.790 --> 00:03:27.999 position:50% align:center
If I learn about love,

00:03:28.083 --> 00:03:30.543 position:50% align:center
maybe I'll understand
my parents better.

00:03:30.627 --> 00:03:32.128 position:50% align:center
If I go with that gentleman,

00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:34.130 position:50% align:center
do you think I'll be
able to find love?

00:03:34.214 --> 00:03:35.715 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:03:37.258 --> 00:03:39.636 position:50% align:center
Honestly, that depends on you.

00:03:39.719 --> 00:03:41.054 position:50% align:center
If you think you're up for it,

00:03:41.137 --> 00:03:43.598 position:50% align:center
I'd be happy to give you
this case to work on.

00:03:43.682 --> 00:03:45.266 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Yes, please. I'd like that.

00:03:45.350 --> 00:03:47.811 position:50% align:center
Done. Hey, Shiki. Akira.

00:03:47.894 --> 00:03:49.688 position:50% align:center
I expect you to
offer him support.

00:03:49.771 --> 00:03:51.398 position:50% align:center
Sounds like a blast.

00:03:51.481 --> 00:03:53.066 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
And, uh, kitsune girl.

00:03:53.149 --> 00:03:54.150 position:50% align:center
It's Kon.

00:03:54.234 --> 00:03:56.027 position:50% align:center
Kon, right. You're still
hanging around

00:03:56.111 --> 00:03:57.862 position:50% align:center
cause you want
Kabane's head, yeah?

00:03:57.946 --> 00:03:59.698 position:50% align:center
Well, if you'll help out
with this next job,

00:03:59.781 --> 00:04:01.241 position:50% align:center
I'll give it to you as a reward.

00:04:01.324 --> 00:04:02.200 position:50% align:center
Do you really mean that?

00:04:02.283 --> 00:04:04.994 position:50% align:center
Inugami, what're you saying?

00:04:05.078 --> 00:04:08.164 position:50% align:center
You cannot be serious, right?
You do have something in mind?

00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:10.000 position:50% align:center
Don't blow a
blood vessel, buddy.

00:04:10.083 --> 00:04:12.377 position:50% align:center
Besides. If you're
learning about love,

00:04:12.460 --> 00:04:14.587 position:50% align:center
it might help to have
multiple perspectives.

00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:17.507 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] You're getting a kick
out of this, aren't you?

00:04:17.590 --> 00:04:18.967 position:50% align:center
[gasps lightly]

00:04:19.050 --> 00:04:21.469 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI] Sir. If you're
comfortable with my associates,

00:04:21.553 --> 00:04:24.055 position:50% align:center
we can assist you with your
romantic troubles, cheap.

00:04:24.139 --> 00:04:25.306 position:50% align:center
Sound good?

00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:28.518 position:50% align:center
But they're children.
That's not gonna work.

00:04:28.601 --> 00:04:30.687 position:50% align:center
[KABANE] I promise we will
accomplish our mission.

00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:33.815 position:50% align:center
Sure, but that's not
what the issue is.

00:04:33.898 --> 00:04:35.942 position:50% align:center
Nah, whatever.

00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:37.861 position:50% align:center
Does tomorrow work
for you guys?

00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:39.988 position:50% align:center
Oh, by the way,
my name is Yoruno.

00:04:40.071 --> 00:04:42.824 position:50% align:center
Tomorrow night near
Shinjuku Station's east exit.

00:04:42.907 --> 00:04:44.701 position:50% align:center
--Huh?
--[MOUSE squeaks]

00:04:44.784 --> 00:04:47.370 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO hisses]

00:04:47.454 --> 00:04:48.788 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:04:51.708 --> 00:04:53.376 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:55.253 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA, SHIKI groan]

00:04:55.337 --> 00:04:56.629 position:50% align:center
Sorry about that.

00:04:56.713 --> 00:04:59.382 position:50% align:center
When I saw the mouse,
I couldn't stop myself.

00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:02.552 position:50% align:center
It's just that I'm collecting
these things so someday,

00:05:02.635 --> 00:05:04.220 position:50% align:center
I can gift them to my girl.

00:05:04.304 --> 00:05:06.556 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA gags]
I'll be in the restroom!

00:05:06.639 --> 00:05:08.850 position:50% align:center
Ah, fun, feline possession.

00:05:08.933 --> 00:05:10.018 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Feline?

00:05:10.101 --> 00:05:12.187 position:50% align:center
This is the work
of a nekomata.

00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:14.522 position:50% align:center
A kemono that turns into
an attractive human

00:05:14.606 --> 00:05:15.982 position:50% align:center
to seduce people.

00:05:16.066 --> 00:05:18.693 position:50% align:center
I doubt this love
will bear fruit.

00:05:18.777 --> 00:05:22.072 position:50% align:center
I don't understand. Is love
something that grows on trees?

00:05:22.155 --> 00:05:23.948 position:50% align:center
Hard to explain, but sure.

00:05:24.032 --> 00:05:25.283 position:50% align:center
[MICE squeak]

00:05:25.367 --> 00:05:28.078 position:50% align:center
[KON] I caught these mice
for you. Head, please.

00:05:28.161 --> 00:05:30.663 position:50% align:center
All right, kid. I think it's
time for a little review

00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:32.832 position:50% align:center
of what this job actually is.

00:05:34.167 --> 00:05:37.420 position:50% align:center
[sighs]
That was horrifying.

00:05:37.504 --> 00:05:39.047 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
Akira.

00:05:39.130 --> 00:05:41.341 position:50% align:center
You should think about
sitting this one out.

00:05:41.424 --> 00:05:43.843 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
Huh? But why?

00:05:43.927 --> 00:05:47.430 position:50% align:center
You've never been great with
"scary" or "disgusting" stuff.

00:05:47.514 --> 00:05:48.932 position:50% align:center
If you guys were in a pinch,

00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:51.601 position:50% align:center
could you help if it
meant facing your fear?

00:05:51.685 --> 00:05:54.354 position:50% align:center
Well. I don't know.

00:05:54.437 --> 00:05:55.480 position:50% align:center
Why don't you give me a hand

00:05:55.563 --> 00:05:58.274 position:50% align:center
around the office
tomorrow, 'kay?

00:06:00.235 --> 00:06:02.862 position:50% align:center
So, I'm just in the way, then?

00:06:02.946 --> 00:06:05.198 position:50% align:center
No, of course not,
not in the least.

00:06:05.281 --> 00:06:08.493 position:50% align:center
If we face something cute,
you're our guy, right, champ?

00:06:08.576 --> 00:06:10.412 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I guess that's true!

00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:12.372 position:50% align:center
I'll do my best with
the office work.

00:06:12.455 --> 00:06:14.499 position:50% align:center
I have some really cute
labels I've been saving

00:06:14.582 --> 00:06:16.126 position:50% align:center
that have alpacas on them!

00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:18.169 position:50% align:center
Have you got any tanuki?

00:06:19.796 --> 00:06:21.923 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO] She works at
that place over there.

00:06:22.007 --> 00:06:23.675 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Mature audiences!

00:06:23.758 --> 00:06:24.926 position:50% align:center
Uh, what does that mean?

00:06:25.010 --> 00:06:27.762 position:50% align:center
To be "Mature" means to
be ripe or fully-grown.

00:06:27.846 --> 00:06:29.389 position:50% align:center
I read it in the paper.

00:06:29.472 --> 00:06:31.057 position:50% align:center
What's the woman called?

00:06:31.141 --> 00:06:33.893 position:50% align:center
Just Mao. This is her.

00:06:33.977 --> 00:06:34.811 position:50% align:center
Kay, we're goin' in.

00:06:34.894 --> 00:06:36.312 position:50% align:center
H-Hold on!

00:06:36.396 --> 00:06:38.023 position:50% align:center
Why? We're not getting
anything done here.

00:06:38.106 --> 00:06:40.567 position:50% align:center
You haven't thought things
through at all, that's why!

00:06:40.650 --> 00:06:42.277 position:50% align:center
It's an establishment
for adults,

00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:43.903 position:50% align:center
so children can't go in.

00:06:43.987 --> 00:06:45.488 position:50% align:center
Huh. I didn't know that.

00:06:45.572 --> 00:06:46.781 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO]
Besides,

00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:49.200 position:50% align:center
her shift should be wrapping
up any minute now.

00:06:49.284 --> 00:06:50.910 position:50% align:center
But it's the strangest thing.

00:06:50.994 --> 00:06:52.495 position:50% align:center
I've waited for her
outside before,

00:06:52.579 --> 00:06:54.664 position:50% align:center
but I've never
actually seen her, like,

00:06:54.748 --> 00:06:56.791 position:50% align:center
walk out of the building.

00:06:59.794 --> 00:07:01.129 position:50% align:center
A cat.

00:07:01.212 --> 00:07:04.466 position:50% align:center
We're dealing with a nekomata.
Guess that checks out.

00:07:04.549 --> 00:07:06.301 position:50% align:center
Cool, should we go
catch it and eat it?

00:07:06.384 --> 00:07:08.803 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI sisghs]
That's our target, you dummy.

00:07:08.887 --> 00:07:10.013 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO]
Hm?

00:07:10.096 --> 00:07:15.101 position:50% align:center
[MAO hums]

00:07:15.935 --> 00:07:18.521 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
S'cuse me, are you Mao?

00:07:18.605 --> 00:07:20.565 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry if we startled you.

00:07:20.648 --> 00:07:23.568 position:50% align:center
We're from the Inugami
Strangeness Counseling office.

00:07:23.651 --> 00:07:24.986 position:50% align:center
[MAO]
Inugami?

00:07:25.070 --> 00:07:27.739 position:50% align:center
This whole situation
feels ridiculous.

00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:31.659 position:50% align:center
Oh, the kemonoist?
I've heard stories about him.

00:07:31.743 --> 00:07:33.912 position:50% align:center
Is there something special
you need from me?

00:07:33.995 --> 00:07:35.914 position:50% align:center
We have a client
here named Yoruno.

00:07:35.997 --> 00:07:38.124 position:50% align:center
He says he's fallen in love
with you and that he wants

00:07:38.208 --> 00:07:40.377 position:50% align:center
to know more about you,
so we're helping him.

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:43.380 position:50% align:center
How is Mao's voice
coming from a cat?

00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:47.759 position:50% align:center
Oh, you, huh? Meow I understand.

00:07:47.842 --> 00:07:49.219 position:50% align:center
What the--?

00:07:53.056 --> 00:07:54.474 position:50% align:center
Meow!

00:07:54.557 --> 00:07:55.684 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO]
It's you!

00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:57.018 position:50% align:center
You didn't have to go
through the trouble

00:07:57.102 --> 00:07:58.770 position:50% align:center
of hiring a detective, hun.

00:07:58.853 --> 00:08:02.357 position:50% align:center
I was going to have you join
these fellas before much longer.

00:08:02.440 --> 00:08:06.111 position:50% align:center
It's pretty tough getting by
as a big city kitty, you know.

00:08:06.194 --> 00:08:09.280 position:50% align:center
But don't worry, I'll make
sure to look after you.

00:08:09.364 --> 00:08:11.074 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Those cats!

00:08:11.157 --> 00:08:14.828 position:50% align:center
[MAO] Former customers.
Just like your buddy over there.

00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:16.329 position:50% align:center
This is weird, though.

00:08:16.413 --> 00:08:17.580 position:50% align:center
If you aren't a cat yet,

00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:20.750 position:50% align:center
that means you haven't
been entirely seduced.

00:08:20.834 --> 00:08:22.752 position:50% align:center
He hasn't been seduced by you.

00:08:22.836 --> 00:08:24.170 position:50% align:center
[MAO]
Oh?

00:08:24.254 --> 00:08:25.714 position:50% align:center
He loves you.

00:08:25.797 --> 00:08:27.215 position:50% align:center
Loves me?

00:08:27.298 --> 00:08:30.218 position:50% align:center
[laughs] Well that's
a real shame, then!

00:08:30.301 --> 00:08:31.845 position:50% align:center
As you can see, I'm a neko--

00:08:33.555 --> 00:08:34.347 position:50% align:center
Caught you.

00:08:34.431 --> 00:08:36.307 position:50% align:center
[MAO grunts]

00:08:36.391 --> 00:08:38.268 position:50% align:center
Woah. How'd you do that?

00:08:38.351 --> 00:08:39.561 position:50% align:center
Pretty good.

00:08:39.644 --> 00:08:40.854 position:50% align:center
[KON]
I know.

00:08:42.313 --> 00:08:43.732 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO gasps]

00:08:43.815 --> 00:08:46.443 position:50% align:center
Okay, here's your target.
Now you can state your terms.

00:08:46.526 --> 00:08:49.612 position:50% align:center
But, uh... I don't... I can't.

00:08:51.406 --> 00:08:53.158 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:08:53.241 --> 00:08:55.493 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO]
I-It feels crazy.

00:08:55.577 --> 00:08:57.996 position:50% align:center
But you really are Mao,
aren't you?

00:08:58.079 --> 00:09:00.290 position:50% align:center
This may be weird,
but these are some mice

00:09:00.373 --> 00:09:02.167 position:50% align:center
that I caught and have
been saving for you.

00:09:02.250 --> 00:09:04.461 position:50% align:center
Would you do me the honor
of accepting them?

00:09:04.544 --> 00:09:05.962 position:50% align:center
[MAO gasps]

00:09:06.046 --> 00:09:09.549 position:50% align:center
[YORUNO] Before I met you,
I was such a sad and lonely guy.

00:09:09.632 --> 00:09:12.552 position:50% align:center
I didn't have any friends,
or even hobbies.

00:09:12.635 --> 00:09:14.679 position:50% align:center
I was always by myself.

00:09:14.763 --> 00:09:16.348 position:50% align:center
Going through the
motions every day

00:09:16.431 --> 00:09:19.392 position:50% align:center
and trying to pretend
that was a life.

00:09:19.476 --> 00:09:20.685 position:50% align:center
Mao, the thing is...

00:09:20.769 --> 00:09:22.812 position:50% align:center
...you're the first ray
of light I've ever had.

00:09:22.896 --> 00:09:25.523 position:50% align:center
That's the honest truth.

00:09:25.607 --> 00:09:27.484 position:50% align:center
Please, will you
turn me into a cat?

00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:30.779 position:50% align:center
From now on, I want
to live only for you.

00:09:30.862 --> 00:09:35.075 position:50% align:center
I don't have any attachment
to my human life. I promise.

00:09:35.158 --> 00:09:36.743 position:50% align:center
[gasps lightly]

00:09:39.162 --> 00:09:41.539 position:50% align:center
[KABANE] Do you think we
fulfilled the client's request?

00:09:41.623 --> 00:09:42.957 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Who knows?

00:09:43.041 --> 00:09:45.960 position:50% align:center
But given the way things went...

00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:48.338 position:50% align:center
Aw shoot, those
human-faced cats.

00:09:48.421 --> 00:09:50.757 position:50% align:center
I guess we'll need
to report 'em, huh?

00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:54.094 position:50% align:center
You should know, I'm not leaving
until I have your head, Kabane.

00:09:54.177 --> 00:09:56.262 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Oh, that's right.

00:09:56.346 --> 00:09:58.807 position:50% align:center
How're you gonna solve
that one, Inugami?

00:10:00.642 --> 00:10:02.394 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
A deal is a deal.

00:10:02.477 --> 00:10:04.562 position:50% align:center
Okay, Kon, I want you
to close your eyes

00:10:04.646 --> 00:10:05.939 position:50% align:center
until I say to open them.

00:10:06.022 --> 00:10:08.692 position:50% align:center
[KON sighs]
Fine, understood.

00:10:08.775 --> 00:10:13.405 position:50% align:center
Let's see... I guess
this will work.

